      <html:p>This is a sample of the lrrl writing system. The concept is to reduce the cognitive workload of tracking all the way back to the beginning of the next line. In lrrl, you're always scanning just one character at a time.</html:p>
      <html:p>My next step is a simple interface that times how long it takes to read a given number of words. I'd like to track how people's reading performance increases as they become habituated to words written backwards.</html:p>
